{"article_id":"qOOeaH5mVGVbiIIf","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Can A 'Fiscal Cliff ' Deal Be Both In And Out Of Reach ?","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"Yes","depth":3},{"id":2,"text":"The face-to-face meeting at the White House Sunday between President Obama and House Speaker John Boehner has led to analyses such as these this morning :","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"-- `` The contours of a deal","depth":10},{"id":4,"text":"to avert the year-end fiscal cliff","depth":10},{"id":5,"text":"are becoming increasingly clear .","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"But progress has been slow ,","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"and time is running out","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"for leaders to seal an agreement","depth":11},{"id":9,"text":"and sell it to restless lawmakers","depth":12},{"id":10,"text":"who so far have been given little information . ''","depth":12},{"id":11,"text":"( The Washington Post )","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"-- `` The disclosure of the meeting indicated","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"that private discussions continue in the face of Republican leaders ' public statements","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"deploring the lack of progress and the president 's refusal so far","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"to specify the sort of deep , long-term reductions in spending for social programs","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"that they insist upon as a condition of their support","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"for raising taxes on high earners . ''","depth":11},{"id":18,"text":"( The New York Times )","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"-- `` The lines are clear :","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"Obama says","depth":13},{"id":21,"text":"a deal will not get done","depth":14},{"id":22,"text":"unless tax rates increase on top earners .","depth":14},{"id":23,"text":"Boehner says","depth":13},{"id":24,"text":"he 's opposed to tax rate increases on anyone .","depth":13},{"id":25,"text":"But in recent days , the options seem to have narrowed for Republicans .","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"Democrats have held firm on rate increases ,","depth":13},{"id":27,"text":"while a few Republicans have slowly peeled away .","depth":13},{"id":28,"text":"For example , Sen. Bob Corker","depth":15},{"id":29,"text":"( R-Tenn. )","depth":15},{"id":30,"text":"on Sunday indicated","depth":14},{"id":31,"text":"he would let taxes rise on top earners . ''","depth":13},{"id":32,"text":"( Politico )","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"-- `` For now , the bulk of attention is on the specifics of a deal .","depth":14},{"id":34,"text":"But speculation about details can obscure the bigger picture .","depth":14},{"id":35,"text":"An agreement hovers within reach .","depth":14},{"id":36,"text":"It could be expansive and historic ,","depth":15},{"id":37,"text":"and would come at a time","depth":16},{"id":38,"text":"when Washington is accused of being small-minded and sclerotic . ''","depth":16},{"id":39,"text":"( The Hill )","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"-- `` The meeting marks one of the first positive signs in days","depth":13},{"id":41,"text":"that negotiations may be moving forward in some degree . ''","depth":13},{"id":42,"text":"( NPR 's Kirk Siegler , for our Newscast )","depth":12},{"id":43,"text":"So what might a deal","depth":6},{"id":44,"text":"to avert going over the so-called fiscal cliff of expiring tax cuts and sharp spending reductions","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"that kick in a year 's end","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"look like ?","depth":5},{"id":47,"text":"The Associated Press reports","depth":4},{"id":48,"text":"that :","depth":5},{"id":49,"text":"`` Obama has been pushing higher tax rates on the wealthiest Americans as one way","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"to reduce the deficit","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"- a position","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"Boehner and other House Republicans have been steadfastly against .","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"Republicans are demanding steeper cuts in costly government entitlement programs like Medicare and Social Security . `` One GOP senator said Sunday","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"that Senate Republicans would probably agree to higher tax rates on the wealthiest Americans","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"if it meant getting a chance","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"to overhaul entitlement programs . ``","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"The comments by Bob Corker of Tennessee","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"- a fiscal conservative","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"who has been gaining stature in the Senate as a pragmatic deal broker -","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"puts new pressure on Boehner and other Republican leaders to rethink their long-held assertion","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"that even the very rich should n't see their rates go up next year .","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"GOP leaders have argued","depth":7},{"id":63,"text":"that the revenue","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"gained","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"by hiking the top two tax rates","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"would be trivial to the deficit ,","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"and that any tax hike hurts job creation . `` But Corker said","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"insisting on that red line","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"- especially since Obama won re-election","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"after campaigning on raising tax rates on the wealthy -","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"might not be wise . ''","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"As for the prospects of a deal","depth":6},{"id":73,"text":"being reached soon ,","depth":6},{"id":74,"text":"The Wall Street Journal writes","depth":6},{"id":75,"text":"that `` White House officials suggested","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"the Obama-Boehner meeting was a positive sign for the long-stalled negotiations .","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"The president 's aides have left his schedule largely open this week","depth":6},{"id":78,"text":"so he has the flexibility","depth":7},{"id":79,"text":"to hold additional meetings and events .","depth":7},{"id":80,"text":"Mr. Obama plans to reiterate Monday at an event in Michigan his call","depth":6},{"id":81,"text":"for the House to pass an extension of the Bush-era tax cuts for households","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"making under $ 250,000 in annual income .","depth":7}],"relations":[{"parent":165,"left":0,"right":164,"relation":"topic","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":164,"left":128,"right":163,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":128,"left":1,"right":127,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":127,"left":123,"right":126,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":123,"left":2,"right":122,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":122,"left":91,"right":121,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":91,"left":90,"right":11,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":90,"left":85,"right":89,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":85,"left":84,"right":5,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":84,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":89,"left":6,"right":88,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":88,"left":7,"right":87,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":87,"left":8,"right":86,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":86,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":121,"left":96,"right":120,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":96,"left":12,"right":95,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":95,"left":92,"right":94,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":92,"left":13,"right":14,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":94,"left":15,"right":93,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":93,"left":16,"right":17,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":120,"left":18,"right":119,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":119,"left":108,"right":118,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":108,"left":101,"right":107,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":101,"left":19,"right":100,"relation":"organization","nuclear